author: Soo Kim
title: Washington Lockdown Exit Plan Revealed by Gov. Jay Inslee as Stay-at-Home Order Due to Be Extended Beyond May 4
description: New cases in the state have recently been declining but "we aren't ready to ease restrictions yet," Gov. Inslee announced on Tuesday evening.
content:
Washington state, where the first COVID-19 case in the U.S. was reported, plans to gradually curtail its lockdown measures, but not all restrictions will be lifted on May 4, Washington Governor Jay Inslee announced in a televised address on Tuesday.
